The mother's school is also part of offices that included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint de Brno is the new headquarters of Arch. Design.
No one could have expected that he would also have a mini kindergarten with everything he needed - walls of colors, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, children of Arch. design employees can go there.
Arch. Design's architectural project company, whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini-maternal business school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially children's age, and it was important for women architects and project managers to be able to get back to work quickly.
At the same time as shorter working contracts, the mother's school is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this maternal school and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-maternal school is financed by means of the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to funding (with 2.8 million Czech crowns), they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years to ensure qualified staff and start-up.
After the use of funding (two years) the company Arch. Design. has an obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted a year and it was the Economy rating company that helped make the request for staffing.
Care for children is provided by qualified staff, a nurse and a nurse throughout the day take care of children. Children can go to kindergarten without limitation of age, but they are more than three years old for most.
As it is a "ministerial school" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day more are replaced.
The functioning of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is individual care and education, the mini-maternal school program is comparable to that for pre-school education.
Children only play there but quality education is also guaranteed there - from beginning to preparation for school benches English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with toys and imaginative games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
