Americans have a new "intelligent weapon"
The American army sent in Afghanistan a new "intelligent" weapon, known only as code XM-25.
Generals think that this new automatic rifle will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and "will change the game" for their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super precise cannon
Its projectiles are guided by laser with a precision of a few meters.
Special 25 mm-calibre ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly broken explosive actually works like small grenades.
Ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it explodes at the target's contact but also at any point in their ballistic path.
It can therefore be used against an enemy who hides behind an obstacle, a wall or a gap.
